<section class="bamboo-section" id="bamboo">
  <div class="wrap-wide">
    <div class="bamboo-grid">
      <div class="salt-compare">
        <div class="row is-head"><div>Per gram</div><div>Table salt</div><div>Sea salt</div><div class="ours">Bamboo 9×</div></div>
        <div class="row"><div class="lbl">Trace minerals</div><div class="cell"><span class="x">0–2</span></div><div class="cell">~12</div><div class="ours">70+</div></div>
        <div class="row"><div class="lbl">pH</div><div class="cell">~7</div><div class="cell">~7</div><div class="ours">12</div></div>
        <div class="row"><div class="lbl">Hydroxyl ions</div><div class="cell"><span class="x">None</span></div><div class="cell"><span class="x">None</span></div><div class="ours">Yes</div></div>
        <div class="row"><div class="lbl">Anti-caking agents</div><div class="cell"><span class="x">Yes</span></div><div class="cell">Often</div><div class="ours">None</div></div>
      </div>
      <div>
        <span class="eyebrow">Hero ingredient</span>
        <h2>Bamboo<br><em>Salt.</em></h2>
        <p class="lede">9× fire-roasted at 1,500°C — a Korean tradition practised for over 1,000 years, now in a daily sachet.</p>
        <ul class="bamboo-points">
          <li><span class="dot"></span><div><b>pH 12 — most alkaline food on Earth</b><p>Supports a healthy acid-alkaline balance.</p></div></li>
          <li><span class="dot"></span><div><b>70+ trace minerals</b><p>Far beyond sodium, potassium and magnesium.</p></div></li>
          <li><span class="dot"></span><div><b>Hydroxyl ions</b><p>The only food-based source — supports cellular antioxidant activity.</p></div></li>
          <li><span class="dot"></span><div><b>No fillers, no artificial minerals</b><p>Just bamboo salt — exactly as it comes from the kiln.</p></div></li>
        </ul>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>
